# Rules and Corrections

This file guides the classifier. The agent reads it on every classification call.

The bot copies this file to `MEMORY.md` automatically on first run if `MEMORY.md` does not exist.
You can also copy it manually before first run:

```bash
cp MEMORY.md.example MEMORY.md
```

Do not commit your local `MEMORY.md`. It may contain private vendor names, business relationships, or correction history.

## Rules

Add organization-specific filing rules here.

Examples:

- Known vendor names -> preferred expense category.
- Ambiguous vendors -> category to prefer by default.
- Local tax or payroll documents -> statutory or payroll categories.
- Marketplace receipts -> classify based on purchased item, not marketplace name.

## Corrections

(Empty initially. Populated when the user corrects a misclassification via Telegram.)

## Currency

- Use the document currency when visible.
- Use `DEFAULT_CURRENCY` only when the document does not show a currency.
- Keep foreign-currency receipts in their original currency unless your accounting workflow requires conversion.

## Notes

- Confidence < 0.6 -> category "Other".
- Filenames drop legal suffixes and use the common vendor name.
